1.title: Sick Dick
1.plot: In the strange world of medical diagnosis, Dr. Sunshine reaches into his bag of tricks to break some news to a patient with a peculiar affliction. Will the Mill's Method prove affective?

2.title: Bastard Face
2.plot: Sometimes, no matter how polite you are, people just don't seem to like you. Is it their problem, or is there a scientific reason behind this? Bastard Face tries to answer these hard questions.

3.title: Butt Migraines
3.plot: Using a modified version of the Mill's method, Dr. Sunshine steps once more into the fray.

4.title: Everything Will Be All Right
4.plot: Dr. Sunshine employs yet another method of diagnosis. Is his intention to ease the blow of the news, or an ill-fated and poorly advised attempt at holistic healing? Who knows? All we know is that everything will be all right. Or will it?

imdb.plot outline: In Episode 1, Dr. Sunshine employs an experimental technique of diagnosis on Floyd, but it might backfire in his face. In Episode 2, Dr. Sunshine breaks some hard news to a patient with a severe appearance deficit. In Episode 3, Dr. Sunshine tries to hone his diagnostic technique from earlier on a female patient with an unusual disorder. In Episode 4, Dr. Sunshine tries to deliver bad news in the most digestible way he can think of: an impassioned song.
imdb.title: Dr. Sunshine's Office
plot: _Dr. Sunshine's Office_ (qv) follows the titular doctor as he employs unusual methods of diagnoses on a revolving door of patients.
